On Friday, September 19, 2003, at 08:17  AM, Brian Tuley wrote:

> Is it possible to access & replace the fuel sending unit this way too?
> Or does it require a motor drop & gas tank removal as specified in the
> Haynes manual?

You can also access it by cutting a hole in the body metal above the 
sender (be careful not to produce sparks!).  There are descriptions of 
this on the type2 web site, and I'm pretty sure I saw a scan of a VW 
shop procedure for doing this on Richard Atwell's bus pages 
(http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/).

